title: Titans sign Looney, move Schwenke to Injured Reserve
text:
Titans sign Looney, move Schwenke to Injured Reserve 
Updated: Tue, Oct 20 2015, 05:31 PM 
The Tennessee Titans agreed to terms with C/G Joe Looney and placed C Brian Schwenke on injured reserve. Looney (6-3, 315) was a fourth-round selection by San Francisco in the 2012 NFL Draft, and played in 19 games with four starts the 49ers. Last season, he played in 15 games and registered the first four starts (2 RG, 1 LG, 1 C) of his NFL career. Looney was a four-year starter on the offensive line at Wake Forest. 
Courtesy: Tennessee Titans Media Relations Department Related Stories
